"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105982","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-04-04","<p>Defra is an inclusive Department, which encourages all age demographics to engage with the apprenticeship offer. An apprentice can be a new recruit or current employee aged 16 or over. However, individuals do have to meet set eligibility criteria to be able to take up an apprenticeship and receive funded training opportunities.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2019-04-04T16:05:44.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105982/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105982/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105982/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-03-28","Agriculture: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, can the member further outline whether apprenticeships will be age restricted or will be designed to entice any particular demographic.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","238340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105983","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-04-04","<p>We are considering a number of policy options for the prevention Green Paper and will be mindful of the suggestion of a skin cancer awareness campaign.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2019-04-04T14:49:12.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105983/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105983/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105983/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-28","Skin Cancer: Health Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department has made an assessment of the potential merits of including in the Green Paper on prevention, a skin cancer awareness porgramme.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","238324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105985","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-04-02","<p>The Department is carrying out a literature review on the factors driving the use of food banks. There is no plan to publish an interim report. A final report will be published in due course.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2019-04-02T15:06:35.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105985/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105985/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105985/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-03-28","Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will publish the interim findings of her Department's study entitled Factors driving the use of food banks.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","238363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105986","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-04-04","<p>The Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government has not had discussions with local councils on grants for Easter community events held in or by churches. More broadly, the Department encourages local authorities to consider supporting local community events. This includes the MHCLG-funded Near Neighbours programme which provides small grants to local communities to encourage people to come together to break down barriers, including funding events centred around a religious festival.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-04-04T13:45:58.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105986/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105986/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105986/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-28","Churches: Easter","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what discussions his Department has had with local councils on grants for Easter community events held in or by churches.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","238341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105987","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-04-02","<p>We are aware of reports that allege that organ harvesting may be taking place in China, including suggestions that minority and religious groups are being specifically targeted. The British Government continues to take these reports extremely seriously.</p><p>These reports include the 2016 update to the Kilgour, Matas and Gutmann report and other information provided so far to the ongoing tribunal organised by the International Coalition to End Transplant Abuse in China and chaired by Sir Geoffrey Nice QC. We continue to scrutinise the situation carefully and review new information as it becomes available. At present, however, our assessment is that there is not a strong enough evidential base to substantiate the claim that systematic state-sponsored or sanctioned organ harvesting is taking place in China.</p><p>The World Health Organisation (WHO) is a specialised UN agency with an office in Beijing, which works with the Chinese Government on a range of priority health issues. The WHO collates global data on organ donations. We will update the WHO via our Embassy in Beijing on the issues raised in the recent debate in Parliament, which included references to the 2016 update to the report 'Bloody Harvest/The Slaughter' and waiting list times for organ transplants in China. It would not be appropriate for us to make representations to the WHO to attend a tribunal that is independent of government, although this of course does not preclude the organisers of the tribunal from doing so.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2019-04-02T16:02:01.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105987/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105987/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1105987/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-28","China: Transplant Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 6 November 2018 to Question 185605, if he will make representations to the World Health Organisation on waiting list times for organ transplants in China compared to other developed countries.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","238342"
